Jay-Z at the Shawn Carter Foundation Carnival in September 2011. Role Soundtrack executive producer Date of Birth December 4, 1969 Origin Brooklyn, New York, United States

Shawn Corey Knowles-Carter (born December 4, 1969), better known by his stage name Jay-Z, is an American rapper, record producer, entrepeneur, and ocassional actor. He is the executive producer of the soundtrack for the 2013 film The Great Gatsby, in which he also is featured.

Credits[]

Music from Baz Luhrmann's Film The Great Gatsby - Executive producer, primary artist, composer

"100$ Bill" (Performer, songwriter)

"Crazy in Love" (Songwriter)

"No Church in the Wild" (Performer, songwriter)

Even though not appearing in the soundtrack, this songs are also used in the film.
